The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, specifically the budgeted versions of the connected dominating set and edge-vertex domination problems. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper involves tree decompositions and approximation algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.RO (Robotics).
